Usage: create_virtual_shape_on_pg_wires [-help]
                                        -layers {{virtual_layer, power_layer[mask_num]} ...}
                                        [-name <string>] [-pg_width_list <string> | -pg_width_range {min_width max_width}]

-help                                     # Prints out the command usage
-layers {{virtual_layer, power_layer[mask_num]} ...}
                                          # Specifies the layer pair which need
                                          # create virtual shapes.  mask ID is
                                          # optional to select pg wires.
                                          # (string, required)
-name <string>                            # Specifies the marker shapes name.
                                          # Default, defLayerBlkName.
                                          # (string, optional)
-pg_width_list <string>                   # Specifies only create virtual shape
                                          # on the pg pin which width be
                                          # specified thru this option.
                                          # (string, optional)
-pg_width_range {min_width max_width}     # Specifies the pg width range which
                                          # need virtual shapes . Default, all
                                          # pg wires. (string, optional)